## 13. Lessons Learned

### 13.1 Root Cause Analysis

**Why did this happen?**
- Legacy configuration assumed port 8080
- Backend moved to port 3001 but frontend config not updated
- Double `/api` prefix compounded the issue

**Prevention**:
- Centralize port configuration in environment variables
- Add pre-deployment port verification tests
- Document all port configurations in one place

### 13.2 Improvements for Next Time

**Process**:
- ✅ Use SPARC methodology for systematic debugging
- ✅ Test backend endpoints before debugging frontend
- ✅ Check Vite proxy configuration early

**Technical**:
- Consider using environment variables for all service URLs
- Add health check on service initialization
- Implement better error messages (distinguish 403 from connection errors)

